snippet.textDisplay:
This discribes the feelings of a boy who is from the 70s.
He relates his feelings and his life with what he sees.
In this case he relates his feelings to the movies of his time.
To the leaders and influences and the super heros of his time.
There are many scenes from movies he watched.
But I can only name one,
Watership Down.
About the life of rabbits.
A movie about survivel, death and fear.
Things everybody faces in life.
We have gone through so much in our life's and many of us learned about pain and suffering at an early age.
But for a child tho, or to anyone who is inocent and new to cruelty and the evil nature of men, it is a shocking and traumatic experience that is hard to overcome.
An innocent, with dreams.
Fresh from heaven.
But torn, buy nature....
But...
That is where the strength comes in.
The door.
The moment you realize that life moves on.
No more being the victim.
No more trauma.
But inner strength.
No matter what you have encountered, no matter the pain inflected upon you.
The super hero comes.
The LEADER comes in.
The one who reaches beyond.
The one who faced death.
And yet still lived.
When I say death, I mean every aspect of the word.
The one who saw evil, but will still reach for what is right!
Who still sees what the real world should be!!
Your world!!
No matter what people tried to instruct into your brain.
You reached beyond.
And then..
There is a new death,
death of the trauma and then Resurrection.
Therefore there is a union between death and life.
This is an individual life and fight.
We should not be confined to suffer the consequences and choices of others.
This is your life.

snippet.textDisplay: Anyone else get that phenomenon where a second listen to a song, at least a day later, elevates it ridiculously over the first listen? I first noticed it years ago mainly with Radiohead, and then recently Myth by Beach House. It's always been a passive thing that I realize after the fact, but this is the first time I predicted it and oh man it HITS. I listened to this yesterday and was straight up bored through 80%, but enjoyed some little parts. For some reason I got the idea to actually pay attention to the second listen effect for this one, and holy shit, pure musical trance. And usually it's more like months in between. Now I'm addicted to this song (but that's another phenomenon - in two days It'll be ruined - I still haven't recovered from this with All the Things I've Done by The Killers).

snippet.textDisplay:
Are you ETERNALLY SavED?

It is sad that man made unbiblical Religious church building denominations and non denominations  today are bad places to learn how to be Eternally Saved for (TODAY). The failure to Rightly Divide Scripture as commanded in 2 Timothy 2:15 leaves us with the SIMPLE plan of SALVATION many times hard to understand. One Sunday it is asking Jesus into your heart, the next Sunday it is being born again or maybe saying the sinners prayer. 

The Church TODAY is made up of a Body of Believers in Christ Jesus alone not a man made Religious church denomination who can not Eternally Save your soul 

The Church TODAY 

Ephesians 5:23

Colossians 1:18,

Colossians 1:24



The Apostle Paul clearly explains the GOSPEL by which we are Eternally Saved TODAY. What we know about the finished work of Jesus Christ is revealed to us by the Risen Saviour Jesus Christ to the Apostle Paul alone The Apostle to the gentiles.Romans11:3 Galatians 2:8, 1 Timothy 2:7,  2 Timothy 1:11

To open their eyes,and to turn them from darkness to light, and from the power of Satan unto God, that they may receive FORGIVENESS of sins, AND INHERITANCE among them which are SANCTIFIED by FAITH that is IN ME. Acts 26:18
Romans 5:12 
Wherefore, as by one man sin entered into the world, and death by sin;
and so death passed upon all men, for that all have sinned:

WE have ALL have sinned before God.

Romans 6:23
For the wages of sin is death; but the gift of God is eternal life through
Jesus Christ our Lord

Sin's penalty is death, but Jesus offers us eternal life.

Romans 5:1
Therefore being justified by faith, we have peace with God
through our Lord Jesus Christ:

Ephesians 2:8-9
For by grace are ye saved through faith;
and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:
not of works, lest any man should boast.

We are savED by FAITH alone by the GRACE of God.

Ephesians 1:13
In whom ye also trusted, after that ye heard the word of truth,
the gospel of your salvation: in whom also after that ye believed,
ye were sealed with that holy Spirit of promise

SALVATION is TRUSTING the GOSPEL of your ETERNAL SALVATION alone.
It is not saying words or a sinners praying a prayer.
It is not repenting of your sins which Jesus Christ already has (Past Tense) FORGIVEN you ALL TRESPASSES Colossians 2:13

To Repent (TODAY)

(Is having a change of mind)

Not works unto Salvation 

We're once you did not believe The Risen Saviour Jesus Christ as Eternal Saviour

 BUT NOW BELIEVE and Trust His one Time Sacrificial BLOOD payment for Your Sins on Calvary's BLOOD shed Cross

The death burial and resurrection 

 The Gospel that SAVES TODAY 

1 Corinthians 15:1-4

It's not  being water baptized Today  For their is only ONE Spiritual BAPTISM For TODAY 

Ephesians 4:5 

When we put our FAITH And Trust in Jesus Christ's FINISHED shed BLOOD Cross work 

We are then Baptized by The Holy Spirit

 (not by man)

Into the Body of Christ 

1 Corinthians 12:13 

Its not speaking in tongues

It's not making a deal with God based on your so called good works 

It is BELIEF in Christ's FINISHED WORK on 

Calvary's BLOOD shed Cross.

Blood of Jesus


Blood of Jesus - What does it mean?
The blood of Jesus is the foundation of REDEMPTION. Ephesians 1:7  Colossians 1:14 Jesus Christ died on the Calvary's cross, shedding His blood, (and was then resurrected) as the only acceptable payment for our sins TODAY


I Corinthians 15:1-4
Moreover, brethren, I declare unto you the gospel
which I preached unto you, which also ye have received,
and wherein ye stand; By which also ye are saved,
if ye keep in memory what I preached unto you, unless ye have believed in vain.
For I delivered unto you first of all that which I also received,
how that Christ died for our sins according to the scriptures;
And that he was buried, and that he rose again the third day
according to the scriptures:

Knowing that you are Eternally Saved is not an experience, a feeling,
or saying certain words. Knowing you are Eternally Saved is belief.
Putting your trust in what Jesus did for you.
Plus nothing.
SALVATION is about what Jesus did, not what you do.
TRUSTING in the FINISHED WORK of Calvary's shed BLOOD Cross as your PAYMENT for YOUR SINS .

Titus 3:5-6
Not by works of righteousness which we have done,
but according to his mercy he saved us,
by the washing of regeneration, and renewing of the Holy Ghost;
Which he shed on us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Saviour;

CHOOSE to put your FAITH and TRUST in what our Saviour Jesus Christ
accomplished FOR US on Calvary's shed BLOOD Shed Cross.
BECOME A NEW CREATURE IN CHRIST 

2 Corinthians 5:17-21 

17 Therefore if any man be in Christ, he is a new creature: old things are passed away; behold, all things are become new.

18 And all things are of God, who hath reconciled us to himself by Jesus Christ, and hath given to us the ministry of reconciliation;

19 To wit, that God was in Christ, reconciling the world unto himself, not imputing their trespasses unto them; and hath committed unto us the word of reconciliation.

20 Now then we are ambassadors for Christ, as though God did beseech you by us: we pray you in Christ's stead, be ye reconciled to God.

21 For he hath made him to be sin for us, who knew no sin; that we might be made the righteousness of God in him.

FORGIVEN TODAY Before you were even born

Romans 4:5-7 

5 But to him that worketh not, but believeth on him that justifieth the ungodly, his faith is counted for righteousness.

6 Even as David also describeth the blessedness of the man, unto whom God imputeth righteousness without works,

7 Saying, Blessed are they whose iniquities are FORGIVEN, and whose sins are covered.

Ephesians 1:7 

7 In whom we have REDEMPTION through his BLOOD, the FORGIVENESS of sins, according to the riches of his grace;

Ephesians 4:32

32 And be ye kind one to another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, even as God for Christ's sake hath FORGIVEN YOU .

Colossians 1:14

14 In whom we have REDEMPTION through his BLOOD, even the FORGIVENESS of sins:

Colossians 2:13 

13 And you, being dead in your sins and the uncircumcision of your flesh, hath he quickened together with him, having 

FORGIVEN YOU ALL TRESPASSES;

The Grace Of God is not a license to sin It is not a cheap Grace The Risen Saviour Jesus Christ made the premeditated Free will choice to leave his Heavenly Estate and was our Perfect Sacrificial Lamb on Calvary's Cross Let us strive to live each day Renewing our minds each day in His word  

The Holy Bible 

Christianity is not your best life now It's not your bank account your material possessions It not about (I) and your Sinful Pride  It is a Simple FAITH AND TRUST And the object of this Simple Faith and Trust is in The Risen Saviour Jesus Christ alone who made the payment for our Sins on Calvary's Cross and rose again before we were even born.

Renew your mind in this Eternal Truth Daily  and be not conformed to this world

Romans 12:1-2

I BEESEECH you therefore brethren, by the MERCIES of God, you present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, acceptable unto God, which is your reasonable service.

And be not conformed to this world: but ye be transformed by the renewing of your mind, that ye may prove what is that good, acceptable, and perfect, will of God. Romans 12:1-2


TIME IS SHORT Our Risen Saviour The Lord Jesus Christ is coming for his church soon

 1 Thessalonians 4:16-18

Take COMFORT in these words The Free will choice is yours with no church building Religious Preservatives added Put your FAITH and TRUST in the One Time Sacrificial Blood payment for your sins on Calvary's BLOOD Shed Cross The Death Burial and Resurrection of our Risen Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ 1 Corinthians 15:1-4 

And were sealed with that holy Spirit of PROMISE

Ephesians 1:13

The Eternal Payment for our sins was made  before we were even born 

Jesus Christ took our place on Calvary's BLOOD Shed Cross and was made to be sin in our place

2 Corinthians 5:21

For he hath made him to be sin for us,

who knew no sin; that we night be the righteousness

Of God in him.

BELIEVE on the Lord Jesus Christ,

and thou shalt be SAVED, 

and thy house.

Acts 16:31

No Religious  Preservatives added:)))))
